    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "This is a good point, and should either be solved on the menu select (plus other select widgets) or symbiotically through the panel widget. \r\n\r\nFor the time being you could wrap the container div in a label already like this:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nmenuSelect({\r\n\tcontainer: '#menu-select',\r\n\tattribute: 'brand'\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\n```html\r\n<label>\r\nBrands\r\n<div id=\"menu-select\"></div>\r\n</label>\r\n```\r\n\r\nThat would act like this: https://codesandbox.io/s/sharp-cerf-c8gz8w?file=/index.html",
